HEADWORD: Smutty
<hw>Smut"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Smuttier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Smuttiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Soiled with smut;
smutted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tainted with mildew; <as>as, <ex>smutty</ex>
corn</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Obscene; not modest or pure; <as>as, a
<ex>smutty</ex> saying</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>smutty</qex> joke, ridiculously lewd.</q>
<rj><qau>Smollett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Smut"ti*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Smut"ti*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

